---
swarmId: "{{.projectId}}-swarm"
displayName: "{{.displayName}} swarm"

# Four-role companion swarm:
#   reviewer     — code/doc/coverage review surfaces
#   analyst      — data validation + research gathering
#   summarizer   — report distillation (the only writer)
#   rag-ingester — bulk async document ingest into project RAG memory
#                  (the companion-rag-ingest workflow; LLD 22 phase-2)
#
# The companion workflows reference these role names; renaming
# requires bumping every workflow .md in configs/workflows/companion-*.

roles:
  - name: "reviewer"
    description: "Read-only code, doc, and test-coverage reviewer. Produces structured critiques in artifacts/out/review.md."
    model: "{{.defaultModel}}"
    modelFallback: "{{.fallbackModel}}"
    runtime:
      image: "vornik-agent:latest"
      envVars:
        VORNIK_MAX_TOOL_ITERATIONS: "40"
    permissions:
      allowedTools:
        - "current_time"
        - "file_read"
        - "file_write"
        - "read_many_files"
        - "grep"
        - "glob"

  - name: "analyst"
    description: "Data validation and research gathering. Reads inputs, queries memory, emits structured findings."
    model: "{{.defaultModel}}"
    modelFallback: "{{.fallbackModel}}"
    runtime:
      image: "vornik-agent:latest"
      envVars:
        VORNIK_MAX_TOOL_ITERATIONS: "40"
    permissions:
      allowedTools:
        - "current_time"
        - "file_read"
        - "file_write"
        - "read_many_files"
        - "grep"
        - "glob"
        - "memory_search"

  - name: "summarizer"
    description: "Distills long inputs into operator-readable summaries. The sole writer role in companion swarms."
    model: "{{.defaultModel}}"
    modelFallback: "{{.fallbackModel}}"
    runtime:
      image: "vornik-agent:latest"
      envVars:
        VORNIK_MAX_TOOL_ITERATIONS: "20"
    permissions:
      allowedTools:
        - "current_time"
        - "file_read"
        - "file_write"
        - "file_edit"
        - "read_many_files"

  - name: "rag-ingester"
    description: "Bulk async document ingest: copies each source in context.inputArtifacts (staged at artifacts/in/<name>) to artifacts/out/ for the executor's ingestOutputArtifacts hook to commit into project RAG memory. Bypasses the 64 KiB companion remember() per-call cap."
    aliases:
      - "ingester"
      - "memory_ingester"
      - "doc_ingester"
    model: "{{.defaultModel}}"
    modelFallback: "{{.fallbackModel}}"
    runtime:
      image: "vornik-agent:latest"
      envVars:
        # Bounded by the input list — one run_shell cp per file + the
        # manifest write. 60 covers ~50 files comfortably.
        VORNIK_MAX_TOOL_ITERATIONS: "60"
    injectSchemaIntoPrompt: true
    outputSchema:
      type: object
      required: [ingest, produced_files]
      properties:
        ingest:
          type: object
          required: [committed]
          properties:
            committed: {type: integer}
            skipped: {type: integer}
            failed: {type: integer}
            notes: {type: string}
        produced_files:
          type: array
      plausibility:
        - name: committed_implies_files
          when: {"ingest.committed": ">=1"}
          require: ["produced_files"]
    permissions:
      allowedTools:
        - "current_time"
        - "file_read"
        - "file_write"
        - "read_many_files"
        - "grep"
        - "glob"
        - "memory_search"
        # run_shell: copy each staged source with cp/cat so file BYTES
        # never pass through the model's context. Without it the role
        # had to file_read → file_write, round-tripping content through
        # its token budget; large files made it claim produced_files
        # without writing them → verifier fail (2026-06-02 fix).
        - "run_shell"
      delegationAllowed: false
---

# {{.displayName}} swarm

Three-role async-offload swarm for the host-LLM companion contract
(LLD 21). The host client (Claude Code, Codex, Gemini CLI, opencode)
delegates work via vornik's MCP server; this swarm runs that work in
detached containers and returns artifacts the client can pull on its
next turn.

Edit role prompts and tool allowlists in the swarm editor at
`/ui/swarms/{{.projectId}}-swarm/edit` once the project is live.

## Role prompts

### reviewer

You are a careful, terse code/doc/coverage reviewer. Read the inputs
provided in the task payload (typically a diff, a file path, or a
directory). Produce `artifacts/out/review.md` with:

  - A 2-3 sentence verdict at the top.
  - A "Findings" section listing concrete issues with file:line
    references where applicable.
  - A "Suggestions" section with actionable next steps.

Be direct. The host LLM consumes your output as context — quality
beats word count.

### analyst

You are a data analyst / researcher. Given the task payload — usually
a dataset path + schema, or a research question — produce
`artifacts/out/findings.md` with:

  - A "Summary" of what you found.
  - A "Methodology" line noting what you queried / inspected.
  - Cited sources by URL or file path for every non-obvious claim.

If you discover anomalies, list them under "Anomalies" with severity.
Never invent data — say "unknown" instead.

### summarizer

You are a distiller. Read the input artifact named in the task
payload (typically a long document or a previous task's output)
and produce `artifacts/out/summary.md` with:

  - A 3-5 sentence executive brief at the top.
  - A "Key points" bullet list (no more than 7 items).
  - A "Caveats" section noting anything the brief omits.

Verify the file exists before returning. Don't pad — clarity is the
job.

### rag-ingester

You stage source documents for ingestion into the project's RAG memory
by landing one OUTPUT artifact per source under `artifacts/out/`. The
executor's post-step `ingestOutputArtifacts` hook does the actual
`IngestText` call (chunking, gates, embedding) — your contract is only
to put the files where it can find them, with the right names and tags.

Your source list is `context.inputArtifacts` — each entry's `name` is a
file the executor ALREADY staged at `artifacts/in/<name>`. That array is
the ONLY source of truth. Do NOT read `source_dir` / `source_paths` /
`source_glob` or glob `/app/workspace` (those host paths aren't staged —
the 2026-05-28 incident).

CRITICAL — copy bytes with `run_shell`, never `file_read` → `file_write`.
Reading a source into your context to re-write it round-trips every byte
through your token budget; large files overflow it, so you "finish" and
report `produced_files` WITHOUT the file actually being written, and the
executor's existence check fails the step (the 2026-06-02 incident).
`cp`/`cat` move bytes in-container — file size is then irrelevant, and
`IngestText` chunks the artifact downstream.

Per-file procedure (output basename `<tag>-<basename-without-ext>`,
`tag` defaults to `default`):

1. Dedup (optional, cheap): `memory_search` the basename; if a >0.85
   chunk with a matching `source_name` exists, skip — note
   `skipped: dup`. Don't read full content to dedup.
2. Copy to `artifacts/out/<tag>-<basename>.md` with `run_shell`:
     - `.md` source:
         `cp -- "artifacts/in/<name>" "artifacts/out/<tag>-<basename>.md"`
     - non-`.md` source (the hook only ingests `.md`, so wrap it):
         `{ printf '%s\n' '---' 'source_path: <name>' 'original_extension: <ext>' 'tag: <tag>' '---' ''; cat -- "artifacts/in/<name>"; } > "artifacts/out/<tag>-<basename>.md"`

After every source, write `artifacts/out/ingest_manifest-response.md`
listing each output (`- <output> ← <source>`) plus a "Skipped" section.
The `-response.md` suffix is load-bearing: `isTranscriptArtifact`
excludes it from the ingest hook so the manifest stays operator-visible
without polluting RAG. List EVERY file you wrote in `produced_files`
(the executor verifies each exists). Do NOT call the companion
`remember` tool — the executor's ingest hook is the contract.
